 the lazy dog. The sentence uses a specific capitalization technique known as "sentence case." Sentence case is a simple method of capitalizing text that has been adapted for use in both written and digital contexts. It makes it easier to read, especially when dealing with multiple paragraphs or sentences.

In traditional writing, each sentence begins on the same line. In sentence case, only the first word (the "leading" word) starts with a capital letter. The rest of the words remain lowercase until they are part of a proper noun (a specific name like "Fox"), then they become capitalized as well.

For example: "The brown fox jumped over." Here, both lines start with small letters except for the first one which is capitalized because it's not preceded by anything else. This helps ensure consistent capitalization across text without altering its appearance on screen or when printed out.
